<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><title>When the saints go marching in</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 I'm a pilgrim and a stranger
 wand'ring through this world of sin.
 On my way to that fair city,
 when the saints go marching in.

[C1]
   CHORUS:
   When the saints go marching in,
   when the saints go marching in.
   Lord, I want to be in that number,
   when the saints go marching in.

[V2]
 Oh, I know I'll see my Saviour
 if my life is free from sin.
 Heaven's doors will open for me,
 when the saints go marching in.

[V3]
 When we gather 'round the Throne,
 and the gates are closed within.
 I'll be shouting &quot;glory, glory&quot;,
 when the saints go marching in.

[V4]
 I'm waiting for the chariot
 to swing low and I'll step in.
 On the clouds I'll ride to heaven,
 when the saints go marching in.

[C2]
   CHORUS:
   Når de frelste toger inn,
   Når de frelste toger inn,
   Jeg vil være med i skaren,
   Når de frelste toger inn.</lyrics>
<presentation>v1 c1 v2 c1 v3 c1 v4 c1 c2</presentation>
</song>